‚ú®üîÆ "I Affirm Who I Deserve To Be" üìú‚úç | I think affirmation practices are both underestimated and overestimated. Some believe they are useless (which becomes their reality) and some believe they will work without doing anything else (repetition + feeling + practice is an important part). And they can also feel frustrating or awkward if it isn't "reality" yet. This is normal af and I experience this sometimes. But one thing I am sure of: they help program the mind/emotions/body/spirit with desires and intentions. Even if it takes time and creates mental resistance. .
.
Because to repeat, practice and affirm* feeling, being, doing or attracting something is powerful. It gives somewhere to direct consciousness, to focus on & to aim for. Affirming desires/goals/visions is very important for the psyche. Especially with staying aligned day to day and making authentic choices (im a lost-ass binch if i don't) . It helps me find flow because there is somewhere to "lean into". And I can feel more safe surrendering into my process and path.
. .
They are helping to transform me. I'm still incredibly imperfect (always will be) and face challenges everyday but I am also always. evolving. And I've come a long way.
.
I also like to see affirmations as prayers to Spirit, The Universe or whatever you believe in. To send out those desires into the universe, really feel them and do one's best to align with them. This is when I get synchronicities, opportunities, ideas, inspiration and abundance. Bc magic is fkn real. #stayinspired
.
If you want & if you practice affirmations, I'd love to see yours in the comment section! üìú‚úç
.
P.S. I got so many requests for the "2020 Manifestion Calendars" again so I have the link for them in my bio (recommend U.S. orders only to make sure they get there by New Years) much love. Alexis
.

New ‚ú®üîÆüåô "My Strangeness Is My Brilliance" üíéüìöüß†" | Definition of 'Strange': different from what is usual, ordinary, or expected. üìú‚úç I think the word 'strange' seems to have a negative connotation. Which is a shame because it'd be so much cooler if we/others celebrated our oddities, quirks, weirdness, obsessions, goofiness and random passions. As if people in general have to act/think/do the same or "norm" of society. Which is REALLY fkn boring. I feel like most of my life I've had a really different way of perceiving and responding to the world the way "most" people do. .
.
For instance, I can't do simple math in my head or navigate my home town I lived in for most of my life. And that has always embarrased me. But I have other things I *can* do, out of the ordinary. I have a unique way of functioning and I think alot of us do. But we're taught what is appropriate, what to like, and which parts of us are "okay" to show to the world. So we adjust. We mold. And we deny parts of ourselves. What if the parts of us we hide are actually our brilliance? Our genius? Weird talents? Or silliness? What if we could more quickly evolve society and the world if we were encouraged to express our authenticity? New ways of being, thinking, and doing things. üìú‚úçüß†üïØüëÅ Just my thoughts!! #stayinspired
.
üîÆ P.S. what ya think of this design!? I'm playing around with my creativity and exploring new ways of expressing it.
.

New ‚ú®üìöüíú "Words Are Spells" üìú‚úçüí´ | & Consciousness is Magic üëÅüß†‚òï. Words fascinate me. As a young teen I started writing poetry, songs and journaling. Bc you can play with words and have fun. But it wasn't until I was 20 that I began to realize their power. I discovered it in a psych lecture in college. A study that found people who wrote down their goals were 40% more likely to succeed at them. "How can this be!?" I thought. But I recognized it in my own life. It's almost like making a sweet promise to yourself and reinforcing what you want/who you wanna be. It strengthens the will.
.
But is it the "words" that have the power? Or something else? Perhaps it is the caster of the spells. The one who desires. The one who possesses 'consciousness'. The ultimate energy and force bearer. Idk why I'm being so dramatic üòÇ but it's just so incredibly interesting to me.. it's fkn MAGIC, man. I'm such a fan of affirmations, visualization, ALL OF IT. That's witch work. On an intellectual/spiritual level. ‚ú®‚úçüí´
.

‚ú®üïØüåô "To Be A Human" üåπüìöüï∑ | When I look at my past-self, I just wanna give her a giant fkn hug and tell her she's doing a good job and that she's pure magic no matter what. But this seems harder to do with my current-self. And I'm learning how important this is. Self-compassion and acceptance. More than ever. I can be so ambitious and set such high expectations that I forget to appreciate where/who tf I am right now. Or to leave room for my "messiness" and "growing pains". I simply cannot ALWAYS be postive and in-flow. But I can damn sure try. And will continue to. But I'm working on releasing the self-guilt and judgement that comes in these more messy moments. To just have endless amounts of love and sympathy through my processes and struggles. And to trust my damn self.
.
My dude thought of an interesting question the other day: "If you were your future-self and you could come to this moment right now (your current-self), what would she/he tell you?" ü§î [answer in the comments if you want, I'm curious.]
.
When he asked that I got emotional and responded with: "Trust yourself. You're exactly where you're meant to be. Stop listening to everyone else and start listening to yourself. You know best. There is wisdom within you. Appreciate how far you've come and be excited for where you're going but be more present now. And practice gratitude every fuckin day. Connect with your loved ones more. They are all that matters." #stayinspired #happyhalloween
.
.
P.S. Art Shop opens Thurs, Nov 7th. I'll be posting about it/reminding. üôè thank youuu xx.
.

‚ú®üå≥üìö "Evolve Anyways" üîÆ‚ú®üôè | Practice. A few months ago I reached out to someone I admire for guidance * cough @the.holistic.psychologist * . I wanted to hide and felt stuck (still do sometimes). But she gave me a great gift. Permission to practice. Gradually. Daily. Making choices from the Higher Self. With the awareness that the Ego will resist. Attempting to scare us back into the comfort zone. But to evolve anyways. Bc the ego will chatter and lie to us. Normal. And I really like to think of it as "practice" and/or "alignment". It feels more flowy and takes pressure off (but doesn't make it easier lol).
.
.
 I released a podcast yesterday w. @inspiredtowrite and my ego REALLY wasn't having it. Messy magic. I wanted to literally crawl in a hole and cried to my boyfriend & friends about it. I even had a nervous dream lastnight that I crashed a giant spaceship and lost hundreds of lives. Half of Earth hated me. üôÉ I realized this subconsciously translated to me fearing losing people's acceptance. But hey, at least I got practice in that traumatic ass dream üôåü§ó. I feel I can do even more "scary" or "new" things now. And know that they will include pushing past resistance.
.
.
Anyways, point being is PRACTICE. New ways of being, thinking, feeling, and doing. This includes so much. Being patient with myself is something quite foreign to me. It is not my nature. But I've been seeking to radically employ self-compassion and patience with myself this year (and in future of course). Because things take time and that's just part of the human process. The journey. That we are all on. It's not from A to B. It's swirls and winds and dots and set backs and jumps. I just wanna embrace that shit. And be able to see it from a larger perspective. And to do my best to: evolve anyways.
.
.

‚ú®üìöüïØ"I Am A Magical Mess" üìú‚úçüíô | What if your 'mess' is your 'magic'? I was videochatting with @inspiredtowrite this morning and I realized something. I'm doing my first podcast with her and it's been an ego battle. Speaking and being heard makes me nervous/vulnerable. A developing skill. & she's been so encouraging and supportive (we've done two takes üôÉ) I told her something like: "thank you for seeing the magic in my mess." Bc growing, trying and learning things on this human journey IS a fkn mess at times. But if things are smooth and easy then I know I'm in a comfort zone. And leaving that shit is uncomfortable, yes. But at least being in it means your birthing magic. A few failed attempts, sure maybe. But risk & vulnerability can unlock opportunities, evolution, new skills, connection, expanded creativity and that is MAGIC to me.
.
.
Tbh, I've been a magical-ass mess most of my life. Always going through some new process (thats being human). The photo on the right is of me in my old apartment. January 2018. Major growing pains. This time period was revolutionary for me. I was tapping into my artistic abilities but struggling to execute. I was desiring spiritual solitude but couldn't say no to invites. I was reading/learning so much but lacking in application. I was chasing my dreams but not catching & having anxiety attacks at my waitressing job. I was trying to create healthy habits but drinking too much. I was practicing being who I am today but getting stuck in old patterns (a never-ending journey). But I am so fkn thankful for that girl. For her evolving and knowing she deserved better.
.
.
I set expectations too damn high for myself and have a hard time trusting the process and divine timing of it all. But I'm seeking to make peace with the magical messy parts of it all. Because I believe that's maybe where my gifts/new skills/purpose/value come from. To go through something can mean great wisdom on the otherside. Lately I've been affirming: I make space for my imperfections. I make space for my human. Because... "what if your mess IS your magic?"
.
.
#digitalart #digitalillustration #magic #mess #magicalmess #growth #evolution #surrender

‚ú®üôèüïØ"Growing Pains"üìú‚úçü¶ã | The in-between. The unfamiliar. Crossing the threshold. Leaving the comfort zone. The chrysalis. The rebirth. I suppose at a deep level, we are meant to evolve. Just like nature. And the universe. .
My growing pains are usually about releasing what no longer serves me, transforming old philosophies and/or becoming more of who I deserve to be. It can be an awkard and uncomfortable ass process. What next? Who am I? Where do I go? What do I do? Leaning into these questions has helped me alot. Just getting curious and praying "hey give ya girl a clue plzzz?" Often it's baby steps. Or just questioning my current reality/beliefs/habits. Also the pain & stagnation really give that extra motivation üôÑüòèüò§. Solitude helps and spiritual practices. Anything BUT forcing myself to stay in that "familiar comfort zone" (that actually just hurts really bad after awhile.)
.
But hey, I've got some great assets. My mind as a tool. My heart as a compass. And my spirit as a guide. Connecting to all that is. Sometimes we get these nudges/pushes from the universe and often on the other side is beautiful transformation or opportunities. Trust. Surrender. Breakdown. Disrupt. Evolve. Get curious. Pray. Connect. Practice. Rebirth. Enjoy. Grow. Repeat.
.
#art #illustration #growingpains #artist #write #letgo #surrender #cry #release #emotions #procreate #procreatedrawing

‚ú®üôè "She Had To Write..." üìú‚úç | I had my first painful awakening when I was about 14 thru 16 yrs old. I wasn't sure if I was an insane person trapped within a sane society.  Or if I was a sane person trapped within one giant insane society. It was like all of a sudden, the purity & innocence of my little girl heart -- vanished. I saw the darkness of the world and felt it growing, like a plague, within my heart. I saw the trauma and dysfunction within my family and realized it wasn't normal. I could no longer relate with my peers or friends. We weren't thinking about the same things. I was focused on corruption, my existential crisis, conspiracies, aliens, and desperately hungry for answers about the universe (and myself). I isolated myself and didn't tell people what was going on. I would turn off my phone for weeks and lie to ppl "sorry I lost it." .
.
There was a rage within me. I hated myself & the world. Except for my grandma. She was my bestfriend. My lil bro and I went to visit my g.parents almost every wkend (rip). They encouraged me to create art and I saw my grandma journal sometimes. Thank the universe.. üí≠‚ú®üôè I used to steal her xanax and take it at school. I thought I was going crazy. My mom tried to help and I saw a psychiatrist along w.her, my older sis & baby bro. Most visits I would go in there, cross my arms, avoid eye contact, and not say a word. She put me on anti-depressant meds. It (personally) made me feel more disconnected w.myself. I pretended to take it & decided to journal instead. .
I often say "I wrote myself out of depression."
I had a black composition book. It provided a space for me. To be heard. To express myself. To feel safe and to (slowly) make sense of myself, my life, and the world. I would write for hours sometimes. Esp during summer. I would stay home alone and take care of my baby bro. It was a way for me to make peace w.my innerworld, calm my confusion, unpack trauma, write of the good/bad of the world & ppl and express the suppressed. I turned to spirituality and dug caverns within my heart until I found light. I've never stopped digging. Or praying. Or writing. Or learning since then. I can't & I won't. Over & over.

*New Version* üååüìöüïØ "Manifesting My Dreams And Minding My Business" üôèüîÆ‚òï" | "Manifesting" doesn't mean *poof* something appears. No. I believe it means setting an intention. Dedicating yourself to it. Taking action. Learning. Praying. Becoming. And aligning yourself. Like a "hustle-flow" type of thing. Not suffocating the dream but also not allowing yourself to become too distracted from it. .
.
And "minding my business" (to me) means not allowing outside circumstances, people, or beliefs to influence you. To be independent in your endeavors. And just let other people do THEIR own thing. To not criticize or judge too much. If you wanna have a positive influence over somebody then lead by example. I remember when I used to force my advice on ppl (ew). .
So I'll be over here... just manifesting my dreams and minding my damn business. #stayinspired
.
.

‚ú®üìö "Opening Up To Divine Guidance" üïØ‚ú® | My "ego"/"identity"/"story" has got in the way of true divine intelligence & my soul MANY times. It's really a spiritual warfare up in here! Head and heart. From fear or love. Lack or abundance. Insecurity or worthiness. All of it. This is why I believe in committing to staying connected to my soul. For me, that looks like creating, praying, writing, nature, meditation, TRUE connection with others, meaningful conversation. Not all the distracting bullshit. The mindless scrolling, consuming soul-less things, or filling time with people out of loneliness. .
.
I just hope that when I create illustrations like this ppl understand that it's NOT all about taking an aesthetically pleasing bath. It's about the message. The deeper layer of what I'm seeking to convey. In a creative and visually-captivating way. Because for me, these moments. Of "soul-itude" have made all the difference. I've finally learned to genuinely connect with my own personal "magic" and the universe/God/creator. This is what I'm advocating. This is what SAVED me and SAVES me everyday. From my "self" to something so much bigger and meaningful. .
.

üìöüååüïØ"What Will Your Story Be?" üìú‚úçüîÆ | We're have a rare Friday, the 13th full moon tonight. Won't happen for another 30 years. 2049. So in light of that (pun intended), I decided to illustrate something on the more whimsical, magical side.
.
.
"What will your story be?" I try to think about my life in a more "big picture" kind of way. As a story. A movie. A journey. I'm so inspired by Joseph Campbell's work "The Hero's Journey". I drew a chart about it on her poster in the drawing. üìú‚úç‚õ∞üß≠ Bc it's so damn easy to get caught up in the confusing, challenging moments. But these are our "Trials & Failures" chapter. Leading to the "Growth & New Skills" chapter. To think of periods of our lives as chapters helps, I believe. Our life really is a story. And us the "Hero". üé®I never meant to be an artist. It seemed like nonsense until my heart started aching for it 2 1/2 years into University. Studying Psych with a full plan to obtain my doctoral degree. I thought that was the most reasonable pursuit of one of my other passions. Plus I enjoy school. I was good at it & I listened to other people & to fear. But I randomly posted a painting on Ebay and it actually SOLD.. a year later. I had forgot about it. A rare thing to happen for a painting with no social media/marketing. I took it as a sign from the universe that maybe... it *might* be possible. I pondered the idea and an excitement sparked in my belly.
.
I decided that I would quit school, stay waitressing and start social media. No clue how many years it might take. If I sincerely worked my ASS off and made GREAT art ~ it *could* happen... But my anxiety fought me so much that the morning of classes opening (at 6 am) my BODY woke me up. I signed up for full-time classes & denied my inner-calling, again. But I forced myself to start painting during that semester (I hadn't since I graduated highschool). That entire semester was a battle and never-ending question of "what if?", "what will ppl think?" & the worst: "what if nobody wants to buy my art?" Being an artist that wants/needs money is kind of taboo. But I can't just eat air and drink rain.
.
I started selling jewelry which evolved into my paintings (i was scared to offer them for purchase). Rejection. But damnit "I faked it till I made it" and posted them confidently (even though it turned my heart beat into a motorcycle engine). Sales were few & far between. & I couldn't paint fast enough for the commissions I did have to support myself. I was tired & became unmotivated with 4 years of slow results. Experimented with digital art & fell in love. Made sacrifices, no social life, researched, & pushed my creativity to unknown magical places. 2/22/19 (222 = trust) February of this year I quit waitressing after 7 yrs. I'm FUCKING blessed  and don't know how long this will last but I'm going to enjoy every drop of this. I cry often. Pray everyday. And want to thank YOU. For being here & connecting to the art of my soul. My life.
